Manchester United reached agreement
to sign Crystal Palace winger Wilfried Zaha, the Premier League
leader said on its website.  Zaha, 20, will join United in July, the soccer club said
without disclosing financial terms of the deal. Palace said on
its website that Zaha has been loaned back to the club for the
remainder of this season.  Zaha has scored five goals in 32 matches this season. He
also made his debut with the England national team in November,
coming on as a substitute in a 4-2 loss in  Sweden .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
